version%20meant%20to%20compete%20with%20other%20foundation%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlongside%20Scout%20and%20Maverick%2C%20Meta%20also%20previewed%20Llama%204%20Behemoth%2C%20a%20much%20larger%20%26quot%3Bteacher%20model%26quot%3B%20still%20in%20training.%20It%20is%20designed%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeepseek-openai-distillation-big-tech-trouble-cheap-commodity-ai-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edistillation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20enables%20the%20creation%20of%20smaller%2C%20specialized%20models%20from%20a%20larger%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20reported%20on%20Thursday%20that%20Behemoth%20would%20be%20delayed%2C%20and%20that%20the%20entire%20suite%20of%20models%20was%20struggling%20to%20compete.%20Meta%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fai.meta.com%2Fblog%2Fllama-4-multimodal-intelligence%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20these%20models%20achieve%20state-of-the-art%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMeta%3C%2Fa%3E's%20Llama%20used%20to%20be%20a%20big%20deal.%20But%20now%20it's%20sliding%20farther%20down%20the%20AI%20world's%20leaderboards%2C%20and%20to%20some%2C%20its%20relevance%20is%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efading.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20would%20be%20exciting%20if%20they%20were%20beating%20Qwen%20and%20DeepSeek%2C%26quot%3B%20Vineeth%20Sai%20Varikuntla%2C%20a%20developer%20working%20on%20medical%20AI%20applications%2C%20told%20BI%20at%20the%20conference%20last%20month.%20%26quot%3BQwen%20is%20ahead%2C%20way%20ahead%20of%20what%20they%20are%20doing%20in%20general%20use%20cases%20and%20reasoning.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20disappointment%20reflected%20a%20growing%20sense%20among%20some%20developers%20and%20industry%20observers%20that%20Meta's%20once-exciting%20open-source%20models%20are%20losing%20momentum%2C%20both%20in%20technical%20performance%20and%20developer%20mindshare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Meta%20continues%20to%20tout%20its%20commitment%20to%20openness%2C%20ecosystem-building%2C%20and%20innovation%2C%20rivals%20like%20DeepSeek%2C%20Qwen%2C%20and%20OpenAI%20are%20setting%20a%20faster%20pace%20in%20areas%20like%20reasoning%2C%20tool%20use%2C%20and%20real-world%20deployment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20aimed%20to%20reassert%20its%20leadership%20in%20open-source%20AI.%20Instead%2C%20it%20raised%20fresh%20questions%20about%20whether%20Llama%20is%20keeping%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20constantly%20listening%20to%20feedback%20from%20the%20developer%20community%20and%20our%20partners%20to%20make%20our%20models%20and%20features%20even%20better%20and%20look%20forward%20to%20working%20with%20the%20community%20to%20continue%20iterating%20and%20unlocking%20their%20value%2C%26quot%3B%20Meta%20spokesperson%20Ryan%20Daniels%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221d87cfdc-be2d-4d50-a149-12cd8f0cc6f7%5C%22%3EA%20promising%20start%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnvidia%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENvidia%3C%2Fa%3E%20CEO%20Jensen%20Huang%20called%20the%20launch%20of%20Llama%202%20%26quot%3Bprobably%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzuckerberg-excited-discussing-open-source-ai-jensen-huang-siggraph-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebiggest%20event%20in%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20that%20year.%20By%20July%202024%2C%20the%20release%20of%20Llama%203%20was%20held%20up%20as%20a%20breakthrough%20%E2%80%94%20the%20first%20open%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Elarge%20language%20model%20that%20could%20compete%20with%20OpenAI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELlama%203%20created%20an%20immediate%20surge%20in%20demand%20for%20computing%20power%2C%20SemiAnalysis%20Chief%20Analyst%20Dylan%20Patel%20told%20BI%20at%20the%20time.%26quot%3BThe%20moment%20Meta's%20new%20model%20was%20released%2C%20there%20was%20a%20big%20shift.%20Prices%20went%20up%20for%20renting%20GPUs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20searches%20containing%20%26quot%3BMeta%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BLlama%26quot%3B%20similarly%20peaked%20in%20late%20July%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELlama%203%20was%20an%20American-made%2C%20open%2C%20top-of-the-line%20LLM.%20Though%20Llama%20never%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Econsistently%20topped%20the%20leaderboard%20on%20industry%20benchmarks%2C%20it's%20traditionally%20been%20influential%20%E2%80%94%20relevant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20has%20started%20to%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20models%20introduced%20a%20new-to-Meta%20architecture%20called%20%26quot%3Bmixture%20of%20experts%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20was%20popularized%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fexplaining-deepseek-chinese-models-efficiency-scaring-markets-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EChina's%20DeepSeek%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20architecture%20allows%20the%20model%20to%20activate%20only%20the%20most%20relevant%20expertise%20for%20a%20given%20task%2C%20making%20a%20large%20model%20function%20more%20efficiently%2C%20like%20a%20smaller%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELlama%204's%20debut%20quickly%20met%20criticism%20when%20developers%20noticed%20that%20the%20version%20Meta%20used%20for%20public%20benchmarking%20was%20not%20the%20same%20version%20available%20for%20download%20and%20deployment.%20This%20prompted%20accusations%20that%20Meta%20was%20gaming%20the%20leaderboard.%20The%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftechcrunch.com%2F2025%2F04%2F07%2Fmeta-exec-denies-the-company-artificially-boosted-llama-4s-benchmark-scores%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edenied%20this%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20saying%20the%20variant%20in%20question%20was%20experimental%20and%20that%20evaluating%20multiple%20versions%20of%20a%20model%20is%20standard%20practice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20competing%20models%20paced%20out%20ahead%2C%20Meta%20looked%20rudderless.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20did%20seem%20like%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20marketing%20push%20for%20Llama%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Mahesh%20Sathiamoorthy%2C%20cofounder%20of%20Bespoke%20Labs%2C%20a%20Mountain%20View-based%20startup%20that%20creates%20AI%20tools%20for%20data%20curation%20and%20training%20LLMs%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fllamacon-2025-meta-strived-reassert-ai-leadership-against-rivals-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epreviously%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20singular%20resource%20that%20can%20measure%20which%20model%20or%20family%20of%20models%20is%20winning%20with%20developers.%20But%20what%20data%20exists%20shows%20Llama's%20latest%20models%20aren't%20among%20the%20leaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EQwen%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20hovers%20around%20the%20top%20of%20leaderboards%20across%20the%20internet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArtificial%20Analysis%20is%20a%20site%20that%20ranks%20models%20based%20on%20performance%2C%20and%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20intelligence%2C%20it%20places%20Llama%204%20Maverick%20and%20Scout%20just%20above%20OpenAI's%20GPT-4%20model%2C%20released%20at%20the%20end%20of%20last%20year%2C%20and%20below%20xAI's%20Grok%20and%20Anthropic's%20Claude.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenrouter%20offers%20a%20platform%20for%20developers%20to%20access%20various%20models%20and%20then%20publishes%20leaderboards%20for%20model%20use%20through%20its%20own%20API.%20It%20shows%20Lama%203.3%20among%20the%20top%2020%20models%20used%20as%20of%20early%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EMay%2C%20but%20not%20Llama%204.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20wanted%20to%20cast%20a%20wider%20net%20and%20appeal%20to%20enterprises%2C%20but%20I%20think%20the%20technical%20community%20was%20looking%20for%20more%20substantial%20model%20improvements%2C%26quot%3B%20Sathiamoorthy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c2d77d0b-f2f4-47f6-a043-d0854f66450a%5C%22%3EMore%20than%20a%20model%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20standard%20evaluations%20of%20Llama%204%20released%20to%20the%20public%20were%20lackluster%2C%20according%20to%20experts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20muted%20enthusiasm%20for%20Llama%204%2C%20compared%20to%20Llama%203%2C%20goes%20beyond%20the%20model%20itself%2C%20AJ%20Kourabi%2C%20an%20analyst%20at%20SemiAnalysis%20focused%20on%20models%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSometimes%20it's%20not%20the%20evals%20that%20necessarily%20matter.%20It's%20the%20tool-calling%20and%20capability%20for%20the%20model%20to%20extend%20beyond%20just%20being%20a%20chatbot%2C%26quot%3B%20Kourabi%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTool-calling%26quot%3B%20is%20a%20model's%20ability%20to%20access%20and%20instruct%20other%20applications%20on%20the%20internet%20or%20on%20a%20user's%20computer%20or%20device.%20It's%20essential%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-agentic-ai-agents-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eagentic%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20promises%20to%20eventually%20book%20our%20airline%20tickets%20and%20file%20our%20work%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20told%20BI%20that%20Llama%20models%20support%20tool-calling%2C%20including%20through%20its%20API%20in%20preview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheo%20Browne%2C%20a%20YouTuber%20and%20developer%20whose%20company%2C%20Ping%2C%20builds%20AI%20software%20for%20other%20developers%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20tool-calling%20is%20increasingly%20important%20as%20agentic%20tools%20are%20coming%20into%20focus%2C%20and%20it%20is%20almost%20a%20requirement%20for%20cutting-edge%20relevance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnthropic%20was%20an%20early%20leader%20in%20this%2C%20and%20other%20proprietary%20models%20like%20OpenAI%20are%20catching%20up%2C%20Browne%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHaving%20a%20model%20that%20will%20reliably%20call%20the%20right%20tool%20to%20get%20the%20right%20information%20to%20generate%20the%20right%20response%20is%20incredibly%20valuable%2C%20and%20OpenAI%20went%20from%20kind%20of%20ignoring%20this%20to%20seemingly%20being%20all%20in%20on%20tools%2C%26quot%3B%20Browne%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKourabi%20says%20the%20biggest%20indicator%20that%20Meta%20has%20fallen%20behind%20is%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20reasoning%20model%2C%20perhaps%20an%20even%20more%20fundamental%20element%20in%20the%20agentic%20AI%20equation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20reasoning%20model%20is%20the%20main%20thing%2C%20because%20when%20we%20think%20about%20what%20has%20unlocked%20a%20lot%20of%20these%20agentic%20capabilities%2C%20it's%20the%20ability%20to%20reason%20through%20a%20specific%20task%2C%20and%20to%20decide%20what%20to%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22deef66cb-6fa3-4055-8d4a-19eedb911728%5C%22%3ELlama%3A%20Who%20is%20it%20good%20for%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20see%20Llama%204%20as%20evidence%20that%20Meta%20is%20falling%20behind%2C%20but%20like%20Meta's%20foundational%20product%2C%20Facebook%2C%20AI%20practitioners%20say%2C%20it's%20still%20almost%20impossible%20to%20write%20it%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENate%20Jones%2C%20the%20head%20of%20product%20at%20RockerBox%2C%20offers%20advice%20to%20young%20developers%20through%20his%20Substack%2C%20YouTube%2C%20and%20TikTok.%20He%20encourages%20them%20to%20put%20Llama%20and%20any%20other%20models%20they're%20intimately%20familiar%20with%20on%20their%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%202025%2C%20people%20will%20already%20have%20Llama%20in%20their%20stack%20and%20they%20will%20look%20for%20people%20who%20have%20worked%20with%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Jones%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPaul%20Baier%2C%20the%20CEO%20and%20principal%20analyst%20at%20GAI%20Insights%2C%20consults%20with%20companies%20on%20AI%20projects%2C%20with%20an%20emphasis%20on%20non-tech%20companies.%20He%20said%20Llama%20is%20likely%20to%20stay%20in%20the%20mix%20of%20many%2C%20if%20not%20most%2C%20of%20his%20clients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEnterprises%20continue%20to%20see%20that%20open%20source%20is%20an%20important%20part%20to%20have%20in%20the%20mix%20of%20their%20intelligence%2C%26quot%3B%20Baier%20told%20BI.%20Open%20models%2C%20Llama%20most%20prominent%20among%20them%2C%20can%20handle%20less%20complicated%20tasks%20and%20keep%20costs%20down.%20%26quot%3BThey%20want%20closed%20and%20open%2C%26quot%3B%20Baier%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20that's%20what%20many%20developers%20think%20too%2C%20Baris%20Gultekin%2C%20Head%20of%20AI%20at%20Snowflake%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20our%20customers%20evaluate%20models%2C%20they%20are%20rarely%20looking%20at%20these%20benchmarks%2C%26quot%3B%20Gultekin%20said.%20%26quot%3BInstead%2C%20they'll%20evaluate%20these%20models%20on%20their%20own%20problem%20statement.%20Given%20the%20very%20low%20cost%2C%20Llama%20is%20sufficient.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Snowflake%2C%20Llama%20powers%20workloads%20like%20summarizing%20sales%20call%20transcripts%20and%20extracting%20structured%20information%20from%20customer%20reviews.%20At%20data%20platform%20company%20Dremio%2C%20Llama%20generates%20structured%20query%20language%20code%20and%20writes%20marketing%20emails.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%2080%25%20of%20applications%2C%20the%20model%20probably%20doesn't%20matter%2C%26quot%3B%20Tomer%20Shiran%2C%20cofounder%20and%20chief%20product%20officer%20at%20Dremio%2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BAll%20the%20models%20now%20are%20good%20enough.%20OpenAI%2C%20Llama%2C%20Claude%2C%20Gemini%20%E2%80%94%20they%20all%20meet%20a%20specific%20need%20that%20the%20user%20has.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELlama%20may%20be%20slipping%20away%20from%20direct%20competition%20with%20the%20proprietary%20models%2C%20at%20least%20for%20now.%20But%20other%20analysis%20suggests%20that%20the%20field%20is%20diversifying%2C%20and%20Llama's%20role%20in%20it%20is%20solidifying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBenchmarks%20are%20not%20what%20drives%20model%20choice%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverybody's%20just%20testing%20it%20on%20their%20own%20use%20cases%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Shiran.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20customer's%20data%2C%20and%20it's%20also%20going%20to%20keep%20changing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGultekin%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BThey%20usually%20make%20these%20decisions%20not%20as%20a%20one-time%20thing%2C%20but%20rather%20per%20use%20case.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELlama%20may%20be%20losing%20developers%20like%20Browne%2C%20who%20breathlessly%20await%20the%20next%20toy%20from%20a%20company%20on%20the%20frontier.%20But%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20developer%20world%2C%20the%20one%20that's%20just%20trying%20to%20make%20AI-powered%20tools%20that%20work%2C%20Llama%20hasn't%20lost%20them%20yet.%20That%20means%20Llama's%20potential%20could%20still%20be%20intact.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20part%20of%20an%20open-source%20playbook%20Zuckerberg%20has%20used%20since%202013%2C%20when%20the%20company%20launched%20React%2C%20a%20library%20for%20building%20consumer%20interfaces%20that's%20still%20in%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPyTorch%20is%20a%20machine%20learning%20framework%20created%20in%202016%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffacebook-pytorch-beat-google-tensorflow-jax-meta-ai-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eovertook%20Google's%3C%2Fa%3E%20similar%20effort.%20Meta%20transferred%20PyTorch%20to%20the%20Linux%20Foundation%20in%202022%20to%20maintain%20its%20neutrality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20Meta%20anchors%20another%20successful%20ecosystem%2C%20Meta%20gets%20a%20lot%20of%20labor%20from%20the%20open-source%20community%2C%26quot%3B%20RockerBox's%20Jones%20said.%20%26quot%3BZuckerberg%20gets%20tailwinds%20that%20he%20wouldn't%20have%20had%20otherwise.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aecosgrove%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Eecosgrove%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20Signal%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22tel%3A443-333-9088%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E443-333-